title: Tajikistan Imports
description:
Imports in Tajikistan increased to 478.80 USD Million in July from 410.30 USD Million in June of 2022. Imports in Tajikistan averaged 220.11 USD Million from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 612.30 USD Million in May of 2014 and a record low of 33.26 USD Million in October of 2001. Tajikistan mainly imports alumina for aluminium production, energy (electricity, natural gas, petroleum and petroleum products), consumer and capital goods, grain and flour.Tajikistanâ€™s main import partners are Russia, Kazakhstan, the European Union, China and Ukraine.
